						<p>
				What Is Total Value Locked (TVL)? TVL is the value of all the assets contained within a DeFi protocol. It has become a key metric for appraising DeFi projects because it provides a useful measure of a protocol's general health. By counting all the coins currently staked within a protocol, TVL reveals the total supply underlying the system.			</p>

						<p>
				One of the most used parameters to calculate the growth of decentralized finance is definitely the Total Value Locked, abbreviated as TVL. This is the total amount of money deposited in DeFi, calculated by adding up the total amount of tokenized bitcoin, ETH and stablecoins deposited in the various DeFi protocols.			</p>

